This is a known breaking change. Android deprecated `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE`, and .NET 10 MAUI adopted **edge-to-edge** display by default, so `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` no longer works.

### Recommended fix: handle keyboard insets via padding

In your Android platform code (`Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`), use the `WindowInsets` API to adjust your view's bottom padding when the keyboard appears:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.ApplicationModel;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Listen for keyboard (IME) inset changes
        var rootView = Window!.DecorView.FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;

        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(rootView, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

### XAML side — keep it simple

A standard chat layout works without any special flags:

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

### Key points

| | .NET 9 | .NET 10 |
|---|---|---|
| **Mechanism** | `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` | `WindowInsets` IME listener |
| **Edge-to-edge** | Opt-in | Default on Android 15+ |
| **Who moves the view** | OS resizes the window | You apply bottom padding |

This approach is forward-compatible since it uses the same `WindowInsets` API that Android and Jetpack Compose recommend. On **iOS**, MAUI's `KeyboardAutoManagerScroll` (enabled by default) should already handle this — no extra code needed.
